	(615, 'Public works Department', 4, 617, 'Construction of Building for Sub-Health Centers', 'The construction of buildings for Sub-Health Centers (SHCs) is underway to improve healthcare access, particularly in rural areas. These centers, now known as Ayushman Arogya Mandirs (AAMs), are part of a larger initiative to strengthen the healthcare infrastructure across India. The aim is to provide accessible and quality healthcare services, including maternal and child health, family welfare, immunization, and disease control programs, at the doorstep of communities'),
	(616, 'Public works Department', 4, 6220, 'Public Works Department', 'The scheme contributes to the construction, maintenance, and development of public infrastructure, which is essential for economic growth and sustainable development'),
	(617, 'Public works Department', 4, 6222, 'Construction of Residences for Justice Administration', 'The Construction of Residences for Justice Administration scheme aligns with goal 11. This goal emphasizes ensuring access to adequate, safe, and affordable housing, and upgrading slums. The scheme supports building residential facilities for justice administration personnel, contributing to resilient and inclusive urban development and institutional capacity.'),
