	(655, 'Public works Department', 4, 7991, 'Expenditure by State Government on construction works under CRF', 'The scheme aligns with goal 9. This scheme focuses on developing and maintaining national highways, state roads, rural roads, and bridge projects, which are vital for building resilient infrastructure and promoting inclusive and sustainable industrialization. Additionally, CRF-supported projects enhance connectivity and economic growth, contributing significantly to local and regional development.'),
	(656, 'Public works Department', 4, 8036, 'Excise Department', 'The Excise Department scheme aligns primarily with goal 17, and goal 16. The excise department\'s functions in revenue collection, regulation, and enforcement support sustainable governance, institutional capacity, and public resource mobilization. Efficient tax and excise administration are essential for financing developmental programs and ensuring transparent governance frameworks'),
	(657, 'Public works Department', 4, 8040, 'Construction of Jail Buildings', 'The department seeks to boost peace, justice and social security through the construction of jail building.'),
	(658, 'Public works Department', 4, 8069, 'Commercial Tax', 'The Commercial Tax scheme aligns primarily with goal 16 and 17. Efficient tax collection and administration under commercial tax schemes help mobilize domestic resources crucial for financing sustainable development programs. Effective tax systems also promote transparency, good governance, and institutional capacity, all vital for achieving the SDGs.'),
	(659, 'Public works Department', 4, 8071, 'Construction of Polytechnic Buildings', 'The objective of constructing Polytechnic buildings is to provide suitable infrastructure for technical education.'),
	(660, 'Public works Department', 4, 8167, 'Maintenance of Industrial Training Institute (ITI) Buildings', 'The objective of maintaining Industrial Training Institute (ITI) buildings is to ensure a safe, functional, and conducive learning environment for students.'),
	(661, 'Public works Department', 4, 8716, 'Central Road Fund', 'The scheme supports the development and maintenance of national highways, state roads (especially those of economic importance and providing inter-state connectivity), rural roads, railway over/under bridges, and other critical transport infrastructure. By improving connectivity, reducing travel time, and supporting economic activities, the CRF scheme promotes resilient infrastructure and inclusive industrialization, vital components of goal 9.'),
	(662, 'Public works Department', 4, 8897, 'Establishment of Sickle Cell Institute', 'The primary objective of establishing a Sickle Cell Institute is to improve the care, lower the prevalence, and ensure affordable and accessible care for individuals with Sickle Cell Disease (SCD), particularly in regions with high disease burden. '),
	(663, 'Public works Department', 4, 8935, 'Livelihood College', 'The main objective of Livelihood Colleges is to provide skill development training to unemployed youth, particularly those from disadvantaged backgrounds, with the goal of enabling them to secure employment or become self-employed. '),
	(664, 'Public works Department', 4, 8984, 'Youth Hostel', 'The main objective of a Youth Hostel is to provide low-cost, budget-friendly accommodation to young travelers, students, and groups on excursions or study tours. '),
	(665, 'Public works Department', 4, 9002, 'Construction of Roads in Scheduled Caste Dominated Areas', 'This scheme aims to improve connectivity to SC-majority villages by linking them to the highway network. It also focuses on providing employment opportunities for SC communities through participation in road works and collaboration with programs like NREGA. '),
	(666, 'Public works Department', 4, 9147, 'Employment Office', 'The primary objective of an Employment Office, often called an Employment Exchange, is to connect job seekers with potential employers and facilitate the placement of qualified candidates.  '),
