	(738, 'School Education Department', 17, 9840, 'Construction of Buildings for Educational Institutions', 'The objective of constructing buildings for educational institutions is to create safe, functional, and inspiring spaces that support effective learning and community engagement. '),
	(739, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 1912, 'Criminal Court', 'The scheme supports the rule of law, fair and timely justice delivery, and strengthening judicial infrastructure, all of which are core to achieving SDG 16.'),
	(740, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 2409, 'Election Officer', 'The scheme supports transparent, inclusive, and accountable electoral processes, which are essential for building effective institutions and ensuring peaceful and inclusive societies. By strengthening electoral administration, the scheme contributes to the rule of law, access to justice, and democratic governance.'),
	(741, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 2410, 'Process Server Maintanance', 'The scheme supports the effective functioning of the justice delivery system by maintaining the infrastructure and resources needed for process servers. Ensuring the smooth operation of legal processes strengthens institutions, promotes access to justice, and enhances rule of law, which are core objectives of SDG 16.'),
	(742, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 2450, 'Justice Administration', 'Justice administration strengthens rule of law, facilitates fair and timely access to justice, reduces corruption, and improves governance, which are key to achieving SDG 16.'),
	(743, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 2918, 'Financial Assistance for Libraries of Bar Associations', 'Libraries, especially legal libraries, play a crucial role in supporting access to justice by providing legal information and resources. They enhance transparency, accountability, and the rule of law, which are key targets of SDG 16. This scheme supports the strengthening of justice institutions by ensuring the availability of knowledge and information for legal professionals and the public.'),
	(744, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 3255, 'Assistance Grant to Legal Aid and Legal Advice Board', 'Providing financial assistance to legal aid boards supports access to legal services for vulnerable populations, strengthens the rule of law, reduces inequalities, and enhances justice administration, all of which are central to SDG 16'),
	(745, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 3307, 'Preparing and Printing Voter Lists', 'The scheme supports inclusive, transparent, and accountable electoral processes, which are fundamental to peaceful and inclusive societies and effective institutions. It contributes to ensuring participatory decision-making, access to legal identity through voter registration, and strengthening democratic governance, all key targets of SDG 16.'),
	(746, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 3428, 'Advocate General', 'The Advocate General serves as the chief legal advisor to the state government, representing the state in legal matters and upholding the rule of law. This role supports building effective, accountable, and inclusive institutions, promoting justice and governance consistent with SDG 16 goals.'),
	(747, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 3572, 'Mufassil Establishment', 'The scheme aligns primarily with SDG 16: Peace, Justice, and Strong Institutions. It supports extending judicial services and legal administration beyond urban centers to promote access to justice, rule of law, and effective institutions across all regions, which are key objectives of SDG 16.'),
	(748, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 4006, 'In charge of Election to State Legislature', 'The scheme plays a key role in ensuring transparent, inclusive, and accountable electoral processes, which are essential for democratic governance, peaceful societies, and strong institutions. It supports law-making, budgeting, and oversight functions that promote democratic participation and uphold the rule of law, core targets within SDG 16.'),
	(749, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 4311, 'In charge of Conducting Elections to Parliament', 'The scheme supports democratic processes by ensuring free, fair, transparent, and inclusive parliamentary elections, which are crucial for effective governance, access to justice, and strong institutions. It enables political participation, accountability, and representation, all central to achieving SDG 16.'),
	(750, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 4497, 'General Establishment', 'Most specifically, it aligns with SDG 16: Peace, Justice, and Strong Institutions, as it involves administrative and organizational functions essential for effective, accountable, and inclusive institutions. This supports the broader aim of fostering peaceful and inclusive societies by enhancing institutional capabilities and public administration.'),
	(751, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 5136, 'Grant to State Legal Services Authority', 'The scheme supports providing free and competent legal aid and advice to marginalized and vulnerable sections of society, ensuring access to justice for all. It helps strengthen legal aid institutions, promote the rule of law, reduce inequalities, and build inclusive, accountable institutions, which are core objectives of SDG 16.'),
	(752, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 5171, 'Establishment of Special Courts', 'The scheme supports the creation of specialized judicial bodies to ensure the speedy and effective administration of justice, particularly in complex or sensitive cases. It contributes to promoting the rule of law, ensuring equal access to justice, reducing corruption and violence, and building accountable and inclusive institutions, all central to achieving SDG 16.'),
	(753, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 5416, 'Establishment of Family Court', 'Family Courts help ensure access to justice in family-related disputes, promote the rule of law, and support peaceful dispute resolution, which are key targets of SDG 16'),
	(754, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 5421, 'Chhattisgarh, State Judicial Academy', 'The academy focuses on developing the skills and capacities of judicial officers and staff through training programs, workshops, and seminars. This strengthens the judiciary by promoting efficient court management, judicial education, use of technology, and fostering justice delivery, which are essential for building effective, accountable, and inclusive institutions as envisioned in SDG 16'),
	(755, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 5464, 'Hidayatullah National Law University', 'Hidayatullah National Law University'),
	(756, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 573, 'High Court (Charged)', 'The High Court represents the apex judicial authority in the state, responsible for upholding the rule of law, protecting fundamental rights, and ensuring justice. The scheme supports the autonomy, infrastructure, and functioning of the High Court, which are essential to build effective, accountable, and inclusive institutions as envisioned in SDG 16.'),
	(757, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 6356, 'Fast Track Special Court and POCSO', 'The scheme is dedicated to the speedy trial and disposal of cases related to rape and crimes under the Protection of Children from Sexual Offences (POCSO) Act to ensure timely justice for victims. It addresses the issue of case backlogs in the justice system, enhances efficiency, and promotes accountability in legal processes, all of which are central to achieving SDG 16.'),
	(758, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 7256, 'Computerization of Courts', 'The scheme focuses on digitizing court records, processes, and services to improve access to justice, transparency, efficiency, and accountability in the judicial system. Through initiatives like the eCourts Project, the scheme aims to create digital, online, and paperless courts that facilitate easier, affordable, and faster justice delivery for all stakeholders.'),
	(759, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 7502, 'Establishment of CBI Court', 'CBI Courts are specialized courts established to handle cases investigated by the Central Bureau of Investigation, such as corruption, economic offenses, and other serious crimes. This facilitates effective and speedy justice, supports the rule of law, combats corruption, and promotes strong, accountable institutions, which are core to achieving SDG 16.'),
	(760, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 7798, 'Commercial Court', 'The scheme supports the establishment of specialized courts for commercial disputes, aiming to ensure timely, transparent, and efficient resolution of business-related cases. By facilitating fair dispute resolution and strengthening the legal framework for commercial activities, it promotes strong institutions, justice, and economic growth aligned with SDG 16 and 8'),
	(761, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 8998, 'Indian Law Institute', 'The objective of the scheme is to boost the quality of education at the law institute.'),
	(762, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 9056, 'Arbitration Tribunal', 'Arbitration as an alternative dispute resolution mechanism promotes access to justice, reduces the burden on courts, and supports peaceful dispute management. It ensures timely, cost-effective, and fair resolution of conflicts, which strengthens the rule of law, accountability, and inclusive institutions, all key targets of SDG 16'),
	(763, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 9057, 'Law and Legislative Affairs and Works', 'The scheme supports the development and implementation of legal frameworks, legislative drafting, law reform, and governance activities to ensure effective, accountable, and inclusive institutions. It plays a critical role in promoting the rule of law, public accountability, and participatory decision-making, which are key targets of SDG 16.'),
	(764, 'Law & Legislative Affairs Department ', NULL, 9503, 'Issuance of Photo Identity Cards to Voters', 'The Issuance of Photo Identity Cards to Voters scheme aligns with SDG 16: Peace, Justice, and Strong Institutions, specifically Target 16.9, which aims to provide legal identity for all, including birth registration and formal identification.'),
	(765, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 1033, 'Development Block Office', 'The scheme aligns with multiple goals, primarily goal 1, goal 2, goal 3, goal 6, goal 8, goal 10 and goal 16. Development Block Offices act as key decentralized administrative units coordinating various rural development programs and local governance activities. They play an essential role in planning, implementation, and monitoring schemes related to poverty alleviation, livelihood improvement, social welfare, and access to basic services, thereby contributing directly to the localization and achievement of several SDGs at grassroots levels'),
	(766, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 1167, 'Gram Servant Training Center', 'The scheme focuses on training elected representatives and officials at the Gram Panchayat level to build governance capacity, improve planning, monitoring, and implementation of development programs.'),
	(767, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 1208, 'Rural Mechanical Service', 'The Rural Mechanical Service scheme aligns primarily with goal 2 and goal 8. The scheme promotes agricultural mechanization by providing farm machinery, custom hiring centers, training, and maintenance services to increase farm productivity and reduce labor intensity for small and marginal farmers.'),
	(768, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 2467, 'Panchayat Directorate', 'It is instrumental in empowering Panchayati Raj Institutions (PRIs). In addition, the scheme also supports good governance.'),
	(769, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 2468, 'Government Organization for Training of Panchayat Secretaries', 'The scheme focuses on building the capacity and skills of Panchayat Secretaries, enabling them to effectively plan, implement, and monitor development programs at the grassroots level. This training supports lifelong learning opportunities, good governance, inclusive institutions, and strengthens local self-governments for sustainable development'),
	(770, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 2474, 'Charges related to Panchayati Raj Institutions', 'The Charges related to Panchayati Raj Institutions scheme align primarily with SDG 16: Peace, Justice, and Strong Institutions. Panchayati Raj Institutions (PRIs) play a vital role in local governance, rural development, and implementation of social welfare schemes, all of which contribute to the localization of SDGs.'),
	(771, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 3064, 'Building Construction', 'The scheme seeks to boost construction, which will foster development in rural areas.'),
	(772, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 4610, 'Against Stamp Duty Recovery', 'The Against Stamp Duty Recovery scheme aligns goal 16, specifically Target 16.4, which focuses on reducing illicit financial flows and strengthening the recovery and return of stolen assets. Efficient recovery of stamp duty helps ensure proper revenue collection, promotes accountability and transparency in governance, and supports the rule of law in financial and legal transactions.'),
	(773, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 4855, 'Pradhan Mantri Gram Sadak Yojana (Prime Minister\'s Village Road Scheme)', ' The primary objective of PMGSY concerns building robust, all-weather roads in rural habitations and other core areas. Panchayati Rajs and elected local representatives decide which habitations to be selected. '),
	(774, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 4871, 'Construction of Bridges on the Roads of Pradhan Mantri Gram Sadak Yojana', 'The objective of constructing bridges under the Pradhan Mantri Gram Sadak Yojana (PMGSY) is to provide all-weather road connectivity to unconnected habitations, ensuring they are accessible throughout the year. This includes providing necessary cross-drainage structures like culverts and minor bridges, as well as addressing potential interruptions to traffic. '),
	(775, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 5063, 'Thakur Pyarelal Panchayat and Rural Development Institute', 'The scheme seeks to boost education.'),
	(776, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 5575, 'Three-tier Panchayat Election', 'The three-tier Panchayati Raj system (Gram Panchayat, Panchayat Samiti, and Zila Parishad) forms the backbone of decentralized rural governance, enabling democratic elections.'),
	(777, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 5847, 'Grant to District Panchayats for General Purpose', 'The scheme facilitates the empowerment of local self-governments to plan, budget, and implement development activities tailored to local priorities.'),
	(778, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 5848, 'Grant to Village Panchayats for Basic Works', 'The scheme seeks to foster development in village panchayat for basic work.'),
	(779, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 6376, 'Suraji Gaon Yojana', 'The scheme is a key initiative of the Chhattisgarh government aimed at promoting rural development and empowering villages.'),
	(780, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 6616, 'Grant to Janpad/District Panchayats for General Purpose', 'The scheme supports decentralized governance by providing financial resources to District Panchayats for planning and executing local development activities, promoting inclusive governance.'),
	(781, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 6625, 'Rural Industrial Park', 'The scheme seeks to boost industrial development in rural areas of the state.'),
	(782, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 6728, 'National Rural Employment Guarantee Scheme', 'An employment scheme by the Ministry of Rural Development, providing provide at least 1 days of guaranteed wage employment in a financial year to every rural household whose adult members volunteer to do unskilled work'),
	(783, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 6768, 'Unemployment Allowance Fund Grant', 'The main objective of the Chhattisgarh Berozgari Bhatta Yojana is to provide financial assistance to the unemployed youth of the state till they get employment'),
	(784, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 6981, 'Editing of Panchman Patrika', 'Panchman Patrika, or Panchayat Gazette, serves as an official publication for PRI affairs, decisions, and information dissemination, which supports participatory democracy and inclusive governance at the local level.'),
	(785, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 7475, 'Mukhyamantri Gram Sadak एवं Vikas Yojana (Chief Minister Village Road and Development Scheme)', 'The Pradhan Mantri Gram Sadak Yojana (PMGSY), was launched by the Govt. of India to provide connectivity to unconnected Habitations as part of a poverty reduction strategy. Govt. of India is endeavoring to set high and uniform technical and management standards and facilitating policy development and planning at State level in order to ensure sustainable management of the rural roads network.'),
	(786, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 7490, 'National Rural Livelihood Mission', 'National Rural Livelihoods Mission (DAY-NRLM) is the flagship program of the Ministry of Rural Development (MoRD) for promoting poverty reduction through building strong institutions for the poor, particularly women, and enabling these institutions to access a range of financial services and livelihoods'),
	(787, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 7588, 'Maternity Benefit under MNREGA', 'The scheme is to provide maternity benefits to women belonging to socially and economically disadvantaged sections of society. The maternity benefit is to be provided to a woman for the first two living children provided the second child is a girl.'),
	(788, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 7610, 'Swachh Bharat Abhiyan (Clean India Mission)', 'Swachh Bharat Mission (SBM) was launched in 214 to achieve an open defecation free (ODF) India in five years. This progressed the country towards SDG which aims for adequate and equitable sanitation access for all, especially for women and girls.'),
	(789, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 7644, 'Rural Road Connectivity Training and Research Center', 'The Rural Road Connectivity Training and Research Center (RCTRC) aims to enhance rural road infrastructure and connectivity by providing training and conducting research related to rural road management, particularly focusing on the use of locally available materials and innovative technologies. It also serves as a resource for government agencies and other organizations by offering consultancy services. '),
	(790, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 7645, 'Rural Road Network Management Unit', 'The main objective of a Rural Road Network Management Unit (RRNMU) is to efficiently and effectively manage and maintain the rural road network, ensuring all-weather connectivity to habitations and facilitating socio-economic development. This includes planning, construction, and maintenance of rural roads, with a focus on providing access to essential services and promoting rural prosperity'),
	(791, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 7687, 'Member of Parliament (MP) Model Village Scheme/Sansad Adarsh Gram Yojana', 'The scheme seeks to foster development in rural areas of the state.'),
	(792, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 7759, 'Shyama Prasad Mukherji Rurban Mission', 'The objective is to strengthen rural areas by providing economic, social, and infrastructure facilities.'),
	(793, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 7788, 'Zilla (District) Panchayat Development Fund', 'The scheme aligns with multiple goals, goal 1, 2, 3, 5, 6 and 8, and SDG 16. The scheme supports decentralized rural development planning, resource allocation, and implementation of various social, economic, and infrastructure programs at the district level, empowering Panchayati Raj Institutions to effectively localize and realize SDG targets in villages and communities.'),
	(794, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 7789, 'Capacity Development of Three-Tier Panchayati Raj Institutions', 'The scheme focuses on building the institutional capacity and skills of elected representatives and officials at the Gram, Block, and District Panchayat levels to enable effective decentralized governance.'),
	(795, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 7790, 'Shradhanjali Yojana (Tribute Scheme)', 'The scheme aligns primarily with goal 1 and goal 10. It focuses on providing social security and financial support to bereaved families, particularly those facing economic hardships. By offering monetary assistance and support, the scheme contributes to reducing poverty and income inequality, ensuring social protection and dignity for vulnerable populations.'),
	(796, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 7807, 'Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (Gramin) (Prime Minister\'s Housing Scheme - Rural)', 'PMAY-G aims at providing a pucca house, with basic amenities, to all houseless households and those households living in kutcha and dilapidated house. PMAY-G addresses the rural housing shortage and bridges the housing deficit in rural areas of India, contributing significantly to the mission of "Housing for All". '),
	(797, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 7848, 'Janpad/District  Panchayat Development Fund', 'The scheme aligns with multiple goals, particularly goal 1, 2, 3, 5, 6, 8, 10 and 16. The scheme supports decentralized rural development planning and implementation at the district level, empowering Panchayati Raj Institutions (PRIs) to address diverse local development needs related to poverty alleviation, health, water and sanitation, gender equality, livelihood improvement, infrastructure, social security, and governance. It promotes evidence-based, participatory, and inclusive development approaches that contribute to holistic progress toward the SDGs in rural areas.'),
	(798, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 7893, 'Rashtriya Gram Swaraj Abhiyan (National Village Self-Governance Campaign)', 'The scheme of RGSA aims to strengthen the capacities of institutions for rural local governance to become more responsive towards local development needs, prepare participatory plans leveraging technology, and efficiently utilize available resources for realizing sustainable solutions to local problems linked to SDGs.\n\n'),
	(799, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 7919, 'Chhattisgarh Public Finance Management Project', 'The objective of the program is to: improve accountability in the management of public finances; strengthen revenue administration; and improve efficiency in delivery of benefits in selected schemes, in the state of Chhattisgarh.'),
	(800, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 8209, 'Honorarium and Facilities for Panchayat Officials', 'The scheme aligns with goal 16 and goal 8. By providing regular honorariums and necessary facilities to Panchayat officials, this scheme strengthens capacity, motivation, and accountability of local governance representatives. It promotes effective decentralized governance and sustainable local development that aligns with the broader SDG goals of building inclusive institutions and fostering economic empowerment at the grassroots level.'),
	(801, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 8214, 'Secretarial System', 'The scheme supports the strengthening of administrative and governance capacities at the Panchayat level by providing secretarial support for effective planning, decision-making, and implementation of local development programs.'),
	(802, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 8555, 'Chhattisgarh, State Rural and Other Backward Class Area Development Authority', 'The State Rural and Other Backward Class Area Development Authority in Chhattisgarh aims to improve the socio-economic conditions of rural and backward areas by increasing income generation, enhancing nutrition, and promoting skill development and entrepreneurship among the youth and women. The authority also focuses on attracting investment, formulating relevant policies, and ensuring quality skill development training. '),
	(803, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 8650, 'Chief Minister Gram Gaurav Path Yojana (Chief Minister\'s Village Pride Road Scheme)', 'The scheme focuses on constructing durable and quality village roads to improve rural connectivity.'),
	(804, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 8775, 'Administration Scheme District Level', 'The scheme strengthens local governance systems by enhancing administrative capacities, ensuring transparent and accountable public service delivery, and supporting effective planning and monitoring of development programs at the district level.'),
	(805, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 8918, 'Vivekananda Youth Promotion Scheme', 'The primary objective of the Vivekananda Youth Promotion Scheme is to empower youth by building their self-confidence, enhancing their skills, and preparing them for competitive challenges. It also aims to promote activities that develop and showcase their talents, ultimately contributing to their overall development and societal betterment. '),
	(806, 'Panchayat and Rural Development Department', 14, 8986, 'Chief Minister Overall Rural Development Yojana', 'The objective of the Chief Minister Overall Rural Development Yojana is to promote comprehensive and sustainable development in rural areas. This includes improving infrastructure, enhancing livelihoods, and ensuring social well-being for rural communities. The specific goals often involve poverty reduction, job creation, and improving access to basic amenities. '),
	(807, 'Planning Economics and Statistics Department', NULL, 1430, 'Collection of Birth and Death Related Data', 'The scheme aligns primarily with SDG 3: Good Health and Well-being, specifically targets 3.1 and 3.2. These targets focus on reducing the global maternal mortality ratio and ending preventable deaths of newborns and children under five years of age. Accurate and timely collection of birth and death data is vital for monitoring progress on maternal and child health indicators, planning health interventions, and improving overall population health outcomes.'),
	(808, 'Planning Economics and Statistics Department', NULL, 2987, 'Implementation of Twenty Point Program', 'The scheme aligns with multiple goals, particularly goal 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 10, 12 and 13. The program targets a broad range of socio-economic elements including poverty eradication, employment generation, education, health, food security, agriculture productivity, environment conservation, and empowerment of women and marginalized communities. These components collectively contribute to improving the quality of life for the poor and underprivileged, aligning the program closely with the SDG framework aimed at inclusive and sustainable development'),
	(809, 'Planning Economics and Statistics Department', NULL, 512, 'Sample Survey', 'The scheme aligns primarily with goal 17, as it plays a crucial role in generating reliable and comprehensive data for monitoring and evaluating the progress of various Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). Accurate data collection through sample surveys supports evidence-based policy making, transparency, and accountability in the implementation of development programs. This enables all stakeholders, including governments, civil society, and development partners, to coordinate efforts effectively towards achieving the SDGs.'),
	(810, 'Planning Economics and Statistics Department', NULL, 6474, 'Intellectual Property Rights for Innovations', 'The scheme aligns primarily with goal 9. Intellectual Property Rights (IPR) serve as a crucial incentive for innovation and creativity, which are key drivers for sustainable development. By protecting inventions and innovations, IPR encourages investment in research and the development of new technologies.'),
	(811, 'Planning Economics and Statistics Department', NULL, 7639, 'Strengthening, Evaluation and Research of State Plan', 'The scheme aligns primarily with goal 16 and 17. This scheme focuses on enhancing the capacity of state governments to evaluate and research their development plans and programs, ensuring evidence-based policy-making and improving governance. By strengthening monitoring, evaluation, and research systems, the scheme supports effective implementation, transparency, and accountability in achieving sustainable development objectives. It also fosters multi-stakeholder collaboration and data-driven decision-making critical for advancing the SDGs at the state and sub-national levels.'),
	(812, 'Planning Economics and Statistics Department', NULL, 8048, 'Directorate of Economics and Statistics', 'The scheme aligns primarily with goal 16 and 17. Its core function is to collect, analyze, and disseminate statistical data essential for tracking progress towards the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). The scheme ensures availability of reliable and timely data to support evidence-based policy making, planning, and monitoring at national and sub-national levels, fostering transparency, accountability, and effective governance for sustainable development.'),
	(813, 'Public Relation Department', 15, 1479, 'Establishment of district publicity and mobile unit', 'The scheme focuses on spreading awareness, communication, and dissemination of information at the district level to improve transparency, accountability, and citizen engagement in governance processes.'),
	(814, 'Public Relation Department', 15, 2320, 'Direction and Administration', 'The scheme involves governance, leadership, and administrative functions necessary for effective policy implementation, coordination, and oversight at various government levels.'),
	(815, 'Public Relation Department', 15, 5072, 'Late Chandlal Chandrakar Memorial Award', 'The award honors outstanding contributions in journalism and education, encouraging excellence, knowledge dissemination, and awareness-building among the public. By recognizing and promoting high standards in media and education, the scheme supports informed citizenship, transparency, and accountability, which are critical components of sustainable development.'),
	(816, 'Public Relation Department', 15, 5341, 'Installation of modern communication system', 'The scheme seeks to boost the innovation.'),
	(817, 'Public Relation Department', 15, 5667, 'Establishment of Muktibodh Academy', 'The Academy is likely focused on promoting literary and cultural education, preserving the legacy of poet Gajanan Madhav Muktibodh, and fostering intellectual and artistic growth. By supporting education, cultural awareness, and intellectual development, the scheme contributes to inclusive and equitable quality education'),
	(818, 'Public Relation Department', 15, 6619, 'Digital and Social Media', 'The scheme promotes the use of digital platforms and social media for communication, information dissemination, and engagement, fostering innovation and technological infrastructure'),
	(819, 'Public Relation Department', 15, 6680, 'Cube size house construction loan interest subsidy', 'The scheme supports affordable housing by providing interest subsidies to eligible low and middle-income households for constructing compact and affordable houses.'),
	(820, 'Public Relation Department', 15, 6887, 'Grants to Mayaram Surjan Foundation', 'The Mayaram Surjan Foundation\'s primary objective is to promote value-based journalism and empower citizens, particularly in rural areas, through education and awareness. '),
	(821, 'Public Relation Department', 15, 8688, 'Chhattisgarh Information Centre New Delhi', 'The primary objective of the Chhattisgarh Information Centre in New Delhi is to act as a bridge of information and communication between the state of Chhattisgarh and the national capital, New Delhi. This includes promoting the state\'s various facets, facilitating interactions between government officials and citizens, and showcasing Chhattisgarh\'s cultural heritage, tourism potential, and developmental initiatives. '),
	(822, 'Public Relation Department', 15, 8909, 'Patkar Samman Nidhi', 'The scheme aims to financially honor media workers and support their welfare by providing them with this special fund. The government is taking official steps to ensure the scheme is executed under its constitutional authority.'),
	(823, 'Public Relation Department', 15, 8929, 'Madhavrao Sapre Creative Award', 'The award recognizes outstanding contributions to creative writing, journalism, and literature, encouraging intellectual and cultural development. By fostering creativity, education, and dissemination of knowledge, the scheme supports inclusive and equitable quality education and promotes strong institutions that uphold freedom of expression and informed citizenship.'),
	(824, 'Public Relation Department', 15, 9797, 'Organising information camps in tribal areas', 'The objective of organizing information camps in tribal areas is to raise awareness and provide access to information about various government schemes, healthcare services, and other resources that can improve the lives of tribal communities. These camps aim to bridge the information gap and empower tribal populations by ensuring they are aware of their rights, entitlements, and available support systems. '),
	(825, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 1117, 'Gurukul School', 'The scheme seeks to boost education.'),
	(826, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 1395, 'Hostel', 'The scheme seeks to boost education.'),
	(827, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 1400, 'Vivekananda Gurukul Upliftment Scheme', 'The primary objective is to provide holistic education and character development based on Swami Vivekananda\'s teachings, focusing on integrating spiritual, intellectual, and social growth. '),
	(828, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 1483, 'District Administration', 'The scheme seeks to boost strong institution.'),
	(829, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 2194, 'Special Coaching Center Scheme', 'The Special Coaching Centre Scheme aims to provide free, high-quality coaching to economically disadvantaged students, particularly those from Scheduled Castes (SCs), Other Backward Classes (OBCs).'),
	(830, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 2604, 'Chhattisgarh Scheduled Tribe Commission', 'The primary objective of the Chhattisgarh Scheduled Tribe Commission is to safeguard the rights and interests of Scheduled Tribes (STs) within the state. '),
	(831, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 307, 'Contribution to Non-Government Organizations', 'The primary objective is to support their work in addressing various social and humanitarian issues. The ultimate goal is to help these organizations achieve their specific missions, which often involve improving the lives of vulnerable populations or advocating for policy changes. '),
	(832, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 3185, 'Establishment of Scheduled Caste Co-operation Finance Development Corporation', 'National Scheduled Castes Finance and Development Corporation (NSFDC): Set up under the Ministry, to finance income generating activities of Scheduled Caste beneficiaries having annual family income up to INR3. lakh for both rural and urban areas.'),
	(833, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 363, 'Adarsh Higher Secondary School', 'Adarsh Higher Secondary School aims to provide a high-quality, holistic education that prepares students for future academic pursuits and life beyond school. '),
	(834, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 3673, 'SC/OBC Post Matric Scholarship', 'The primary objective of state scholarships is to provide financial assistance to students, particularly those from disadvantaged backgrounds, to pursue higher education and enhance their educational opportunities. '),
	(835, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 3728, 'Promotion of tribal culture research training and development', 'Promoting tribal culture involves research, training, and development initiatives focused on preserving and showcasing the unique heritage of tribal communities. This includes documenting their traditions, languages, and art forms, while also addressing their socio-economic challenges through various government schemes and programs. '),
	(836, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 495, 'Ashrams and schools', 'Ashram schools are residential schools primarily serving Scheduled Tribe students in remote and tribal areas, providing free education, accommodation, food, and medical assistance. '),
	(837, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 5024, 'Tribal Special backward group', 'In Chhattisgarh, there are 5 "Special Backward Tribes" (SBTs) recognized as particularly vulnerable: Baiga, Kamar, Hill Korba, Birhor, and Abujhmadia. These tribes are distinct from the broader category of Scheduled Tribes and are identified for focused development initiatives. '),
	(838, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 5025, 'Chhattisgarh Scheduled Caste Co-operative Finance Development Corporation Share Capital Investment', 'The Chhattisgarh Scheduled Caste Co-operative Finance Development Corporation, also known as the Chhattisgarh State Intermediate Co-operative Finance and Development Corporation, provides financial assistance and development support to Scheduled Caste communities in Chhattisgarh. '),
	(839, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 5073, 'Minority Commission', 'These organisations are set-up to safeguard and protect the interests of minorities as provided in the Constitution of India and laws enacted by the Parliament and the State Legislatures.'),
	(840, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 5092, 'Jawahar Utkarsh Yojana', 'The main objective is to provide quality education to the talented rural students of Scheduled Tribes and Scheduled Castes.   '),
	(841, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 5096, 'Share capital to National Backward Classes Finance and Development Corporation', 'The main objective of the National Backward Classes Finance & Development Corporation (NBCFDC) is to promote economic and developmental activities for the benefit of Backward Classes, particularly those in the poorer sections. This includes providing financial assistance for self-employment ventures and skill development training. '),
	(842, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 5475, 'Pando and Bhujia Development Agency', 'The "Pando and Bhujia Development Agency" likely refers to the Chhattisgarh government\'s efforts to support and develop two specific Particularly Vulnerable Tribal Groups (PVTGs): the Pando and Bhujia tribes. These tribes are among the seven PVTGs recognized in Chhattisgarh, and the state government aims to improve their socio-economic conditions through various development initiatives. '),
	(843, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 5480, 'Extension of facilities to tribal areas (Article 275(1)', 'The primary objective of extending facilities to tribal areas under Article 275(1) of the Constitution is to bridge the gap between Scheduled Tribes (STs) and the rest of the population by accelerating their development. This involves improving human resource development through education and healthcare, enhancing the quality of life, reducing poverty and unemployment, and empowering tribal communities to access opportunities and entitlements.'),
	(844, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 5482, 'Constitution of Wakf Tribunal', 'The scheme establishes specialized tribunals to adjudicate disputes related to Wakf properties, promoting transparent, efficient, and accountable resolution of issues. By strengthening legal oversight and governance of Wakf assets, it supports access to justice, the rule of law.'),
	(845, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 5488, 'Formation of Chhattisgarh State Urdu Academy', 'The Academy focuses on the promotion and preservation of Urdu language education, literature, and culture, especially among marginalized communities. By supporting inclusive and equitable education and promoting cultural diversity and linguistic heritage, this scheme helps reduce inequalities and foster social cohesion.'),
	(846, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 5495, 'Salary of Chief Executive Officers', 'The salary of Chief Executive Officers (CEOs) refers to the overall remuneration package of top executives responsible for managing and leading an organization'),
	(847, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 5601, 'Bastar Development Authority', 'The Bastar Development Authority (BDA) focuses on the holistic development of the Bastar region, encompassing various aspects like industrial growth, infrastructure development, and tribal welfare. Key objectives include fostering industrial development, promoting tourism, and ensuring inclusive growth through skill development and local empowerment.'),
	(848, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 5602, 'Surguja/ Jashpur Development Authority', 'Its purpose is to plan, coordinate, and implement developmental projects in tribal and backward areas'),
	(849, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 5616, 'Integrated Development of Girodpuri and Bhandarpuri', 'The Integrated Development of Girodpuri and Bhandarpuri is a heritage and tourism-based development initiative aimed at cultural preservation, infrastructure improvement, livelihood generation, and inclusive growth,'),
	(850, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 5631, 'Scheduled Caste Development Authority', 'The Scheduled Castes Development (SCD) Bureau aims to promote the welfare of Scheduled Castes through their educational, economic and social empowerment.'),
	(851, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 5705, 'Community building construction', 'The scheme seeks to boost construction facility for social development.'),
	(852, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 6130, 'Directorate', 'The scheme seeks to boost good governance.'),
	(853, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 6140, 'Student Food Assistance Scheme', 'The "Student Meal Assistance Scheme" generally refers to the PM POSHAN (formerly Mid-Day Meal Scheme), a government program in India that provides free lunches to students in government and government-aided schools. This scheme aims to improve children\'s nutritional status and encourage regular school attendance'),
	(854, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 6499, 'Leather Craftsman Development Board', 'The scheme seeks to provide financial assistance to setup mechanized production units. This support helps leather artisan SHGs and cooperative societies enhance the quality of their products, making them more competitive in the market.'),
	(855, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 6593, 'Rajkakar Development Board', 'The Board aims to eradicate poverty in all its forms everywhere. The board focuses on improving the socioeconomic conditions of the targeted communities, contributing to reducing inequality and supporting livelihood improvement. '),
	(856, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 6594, 'Iron Craftman Development Board', 'The scheme seeks to provide financial assistance to setup mechanized production units. This support helps iron artisan SHGs and cooperative societies enhance the quality of their products, making them more competitive in the market.'),
	(857, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 6595, 'Telghani Development Board', 'The scheme focuses on eliminating poverty in all its forms by improving the socioeconomic conditions of targeted communities. It works towards reducing inequality and enhancing livelihood opportunities to uplift vulnerable populations.'),
	(858, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 6671, 'Construction of Hajj House', 'The Construction of Hajj House is not just about providing facilities for pilgrims—it also serves as a community welfare hub'),
	(859, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 6672, 'Forest Rights Act', 'The Act is crucial to the rights of millions of tribals and other forest dwellers in different parts of the country as it provides for the restitution of deprived forest rights across India, including both individual rights to cultivated land in forestland and community rights over common property resources.'),
	(860, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 6682, 'Chief Minister Higher Education Promotion Scholarship Scheme', 'The "Chief Minister Higher Education Scholarship Scheme" was launched by the Higher Education Department, Government of Rajasthan. This scheme aims to enhance educational levels and provide assistance to children from low-income families. The scholarship is provided to the first one lakh students whose annual family income is up to ₹2,5,/- and who are not receiving any other scholarship or financial assistance.'),
	(861, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 6687, 'Chief Minister Tribal Welfare Fund', 'The scheme seeks to reduce inequality by providing support to tribal community.'),
	(862, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 6747, 'Establishment of Survey Commissioner\'s office', 'The scheme focuses on promoting peaceful and inclusive societies, providing access to justice for all.'),
	(863, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 6749, 'State Backward Classes Commission', 'The scheme seeks to to uplift and support socially and educationally backward communities.'),
	(864, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 6800, 'Formation of Scheduled Caste Commission', 'The NCSC\'s primary objective is to safeguard the interests of Scheduled Castes in India and ensure their welfare, development, and the effective implementation of constitutional safeguards. '),
	(865, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 6870, 'Regarding loan availibility to Scheduled Tribe beneficiaries', 'Scheduled Tribes (ST) beneficiaries have access to various loan schemes with preferential terms and relaxed eligibility criteria. These schemes are designed to support income generation activities, education, and other development initiatives. Key institutions involved include the National Scheduled Tribes Finance and Development Corporation (NSTFDC), State Channelizing Agencies (SCAs), and various banks. '),
	(866, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 6990, 'Ravidas Leather Crafts Scheme', 'The "Ravidas Leather Crafts Scheme" likely refers to initiatives aimed at supporting and promoting leather craft. These schemes could be part of broader handicraft development programs or specifically target leather artisans. '),
	(867, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7015, 'Special Backward Caste Ashram', 'A "Special Backward Caste Ashram" likely refers to a residential school or institution, possibly operated by the government, that provides education and accommodation for students belonging to specific "Special Backward Classes" or "De-notified, Nomadic and Semi-Nomadic Tribes". '),
	(868, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7288, 'Share Capital to National Minorities Finance and Development Corporation', 'The National Minorities Development & Finance Corporation (NMDFC) receives share capital from the Central Government, State Governments, and other institutions to promote economic activities among backward sections of notified minorities. The authorized share capital has been increased over time, and the corporation utilizes these funds, along with its own net worth, to provide concessional finance for self-employment activities to eligible beneficiaries'),
	(869, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7344, 'Chhattisgarh Tribal Development Program', 'The Chhattisgarh Tribal Development Program, initiated by the International Fund for Agricultural Development (IFAD), aims to improve the livelihoods and quality of life for tribal populations in Chhattisgarh. The program focuses on empowering tribal groups, enhancing their income through agricultural activities, and promoting sustainable land and water management'),
	(870, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7363, 'Youth Career Building Scheme', 'The term "Youth Career Building Scheme" likely refers to various government initiatives aimed at helping young people develop skills and find employment.'),
	(871, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7366, 'Civil Services Examination Incentive Scheme', 'The scheme aims to encourage bright and meritorious persons with disabilities to pass competitive exams in the field of civil services. '),
	(872, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7437, 'Chief Minister Child Future Protection Scheme', 'The scheme aims to provide financial assistance to girl children of poor families as well as to promote girl child education, small family norms, increase the child sex ratio, discourage the preference for male child & eradicate female infanticide.'),
	(873, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7592, 'Food grains to hostel residents under Food Security Act', 'Food grains to be provided at the residential hostels'),
	(874, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7605, 'Minority Multi Sectoral Development Plan', 'The Minority Multi Sectoral Development Plan (MsDP) is a centrally sponsored scheme launched in 28-9 to address development gaps in minority concentration areas by improving socio-economic infrastructure and basic amenities. The program aims to uplift the quality of life for minorities by providing financial support for projects related to education, health, sanitation, and income generation. '),
	(875, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 761, 'Girl Education Campus', 'The objective is to provide a safe and supportive environment that empowers girls to pursue their education. '),
	(876, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7626, 'Local development programmes through special centrally funded scheme', 'The scheme aims for the integrated development of villages with a majority Scheduled Caste population.'),
	(877, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7627, 'Vocational Training Schemes', 'The Vocational Training Scheme aims to provide skills training to individuals through local government or recognized training institutes, with the goal of leading to self-employment or wage employment'),
	(878, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7628, 'Preservation and development of culture of scheduled castes', 'The Indian Constitution provides numerous safeguards and provisions for the preservation and development of Scheduled Caste (SC) culture, alongside their overall social and economic upliftment. These measures aim to protect SCs from social injustice, exploitation, and discrimination, while promoting their educational and economic interests. '),
	(879, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7629, 'Centrally Sponsored Schemes for Scheduled Castes', 'Centrally Sponsored Schemes for Scheduled Castes aim to uplift and empower this community through various initiatives focused on education, economic development, and social justice. These schemes are funded by the central government and implemented by state governments and union territories. '),
	(880, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7631, 'Schemes for Minority class', ' implements various schemes aimed at the socio-economic and educational empowerment of minority communities in India. These schemes include scholarships, skill development programs, and initiatives focused on preserving cultural heritage. '),
	(881, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7672, 'Vanbandhu Kalyan Yojana', 'Vanbandhu Kalyan Yojana focuses on integrated, holistic and inclusive development of tribal communities. It aims at creation of quality social and civil infrastructure, and sustainable livelihood, employment and entrepreneurship in tribal areas such that the income of every tribal household doubles. The approach is mission mode implementation of need based outcome oriented projects that improve the quality of life of tribal people and bring happiness and prosperity'),
	(882, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7699, 'Pradhan Mantri Adarsh Gram Yojana', 'he Scheme aims at integrated development of Scheduled Castes majority villages.\nThe principal objective of PMAGY is the integrated development of SC majority Villages.'),
	(883, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7844, 'Martyr Veernarayan Memorial and Museum', 'The Martyr Veernarayan Memorial and Museum is both a heritage preservation initiative and an educational-cultural cente'),
	(884, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7995, 'Central Region Tribal Development Authority', 'The term "Central Region Tribal Development Authority" likely refers to the broader concept of tribal development efforts in the central region of India, rather than a specific, named authority. This area, encompassing states like Madhya Pradesh, Chhattisgarh, and Jharkhand, is home to significant tribal populations and various initiatives focused on their welfare and development'),
	(885, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 8050, 'SC/OBC Post Matric Scholarship', 'The main objective of scholarships is to provide financial assistance to students, enabling them to pursue their educational goals.'),
	(886, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 8403, 'Grants for salary of education workers Basic Minimum Service', 'The "Basic Minimum Service" (BMS) for education workers is typically addressed through government grants, often tied to specific schemes and guidelines. These grants can cover teacher salaries, infrastructure improvements, and the provision of teaching and learning materials. '),
	(887, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 8549, 'Science Commerce Teaching Promotion Scheme', 'The term "Science Commerce Teaching Promotion Scheme" likely refers to schemes aimed at advancing teachers in science and commerce fields, often involving Career Advancement Schemes (CAS) or similar promotion policies within educational institutions. '),
	(888, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 8979, 'Integrated Umbrella Scheme', 'The scheme seeks to boost women and child development.'),
	(889, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 9408, 'Waqf  Board', 'The Waqf Board is a statutory institution managing Muslim charitable endowments for community welfare, education, poverty reduction, and cultural preservation.'),
	(890, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 9410, 'Grants in Aid to Haj Committee', 'The scheme supports the Haj Committee in facilitating the pilgrimage for eligible Muslim pilgrims, ensuring inclusivity and equal access to this important religious practice. It helps promote social equity and strengthens institutional support and welfare mechanisms for minority communities as part of broader social justice and inclusive governance goals.'),
	(891, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 979, 'Sports Complex', 'The scheme seeks to boost well-being.'),
	(892, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 9853, 'Preservation and development of tribal culture', 'Preserving and developing tribal culture is crucial for maintaining India\'s rich cultural diversity and ensuring the well-being of tribal communities. This involves safeguarding their unique traditions, languages, and knowledge systems, while also promoting their socio-economic development. '),
	(893, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 2245, 'De-addiction Program', 'De-addiction services, which are also referred to as rehabilitation or treatment programs, have a primary goal of assisting individuals in overcoming their addiction to substances like drugs or alcohol. '),
	(894, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 2322, 'Direction and Administration', 'Administration focuses on managing tasks and resources, while direction involves guiding and leading individuals or teams toward a specific goal. Essentially, administration sets the stage for operations, and direction ensures those operations are carried out effectively'),
	(895, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 2517, 'Probation Unit ', 'A probation unit is a division within a law enforcement or corrections system that supervises individuals who have been granted probation instead of serving time in prison.'),
	(896, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 2969, 'Establishment of District Rehabilitation Center in Bilaspur ', 'The DDRC aims to facilitate various services including identification and awareness, early intervention, provision of assistive devices, therapeutic services, and counseling. The center is located behind the District Hospital, near the old bus stand in Bilaspur. '),
	(897, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 3921, 'Scheme for assistance to disabled people', 'The "Scheme for Assistance to Disabled Persons for Purchase/Fitting of Aids/Appliances" (ADIP) is a government initiative designed to help people with disabilities acquire assistive devices'),
	(898, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 3923, 'Scheme to assist Divyang People', 'Several schemes aim to assist Divyangjan (persons with disabilities) in India, including financial aid, assistive devices, and rehabilitation programs.'),
	(899, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 4114, 'World Disabled Day', 'The primary objective of World Disabled Day, officially known as the International Day of Persons with Disabilities (IDPD), is to promote the rights and well-being of persons with disabilities in all aspects of society and development, while also raising awareness about their situation across political, social, economic, and cultural life. '),
	(900, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 4858, 'Sukhad Sahara Yojana', 'Under this scheme, financial assistance are provided to the widows and deserted women who are living below poverty line (BPL) to support them in living a respectful life.'),
	(901, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 5257, 'Subsidy Grant to Social Welfare, Women and Child Welfare Institutions ', 'The Ministry of Women and Child Development provides financial assistance to voluntary organizations through Grant-in-aid schemes to support innovative projects for women and children. This assistance is intended to supplement existing schemes and address gaps in service delivery. Organizations can apply for grants to fund projects that tackle social problems, fill service gaps, or provide integrated services'),
	(902, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 5258, 'Grant-in-aid to Indian Leprosy Prevention Association/Institution', 'The primary aim of controlling leprosy through early detection and treatment, initially using Dapsone monotherapy.'),
	(903, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 5397, 'National Family Assistance Scheme', 'In this scheme, financial assistance is provided to the bereaved households in case of the death of the primary breadwinner irrespective of the cause of death. The family benefit will be paid to such surviving member of the household of the deceased poor , who after local inquiry, is found to be the head of the household.'),
	(904, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 5401, 'National Old Age Pension', 'Indira Gandhi National Old Age Pension Scheme (IGNOAPS)" is one of the five sub-schemes of the National Social Assistance Programme (NSAP). Under IGNOAPS, citizens living Below Poverty Line and 6 years or above in age are eligible to apply. A monthly pension of ₹ 2 up to 79 years and ₹ 5 thereafter.'),
	(905, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 5490, 'National Rehabilitation Program for Disabled Persons ', 'Under this scheme, the state government will provide aids & appliances such as tricycles, wheelchairs, crutches, walking sticks, Blind sticks, Rollator, and Hearing Aids to persons with disabilities'),
	(906, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 5618, 'Welfare of Disabled People', 'The welfare of disabled people in India is addressed through various government schemes and initiatives aimed at providing them with equal opportunities and support. These initiatives focus on education, healthcare, employment, and financial assistance, among other areas. '),
	(907, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 5650, 'District Disabled Rehabilitation Center ', 'District Disability Rehabilitation centers (DDRC) are set up in order to provide effective rehabilitation services to the persons with disabilities. The objective is to create an enabling environment to ensure equal opportunities, equity, social justice, and empowerment of persons with disabilities.'),
	(908, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 6451, 'Half Way Home', 'A halfway house, also known as a transitional living facility, is a residential setting designed to help individuals transition back into society after a period of institutionalization, such as prison, substance abuse treatment, or mental health care. These facilities offer support and guidance to help residents develop the skills and resources necessary for independent living. '),
	(909, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 6497, 'Bharat Mata Vahini Yojana', 'The main objective of Bharat Mata Vahini Scheme is to spread awareness about de-addiction and help in rehabilitating the drug addicts. The scheme, through the women self-help groups, conducts de-addiction campaigns at the Gram Panchayat level which include rallies, Prabhat Pheri, street plays, etc. Apart from this, '),
	(910, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 6668, 'Cyan Helpline Toll Free Number', 'The helpline provides accessible, toll-free grievance redressal and consumer support services to the public, fostering transparency, accountability, and social inclusion. This enhances access to justice and promotes equitable service delivery for all citizens, including marginalized groups.'),
	(911, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 6669, 'Chattisgarh State Hairdresser Board ', 'The scheme focuses on regulation, skill development, and support for hairdressers and beauticians, promoting sustainable livelihoods, entrepreneurship, and decent work opportunities in the informal and service sectors. By enhancing vocational skills and formalizing the sector, it contributes to inclusive economic growth and productive employment.'),
	(912, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 6902, 'Disability Development ', 'The development program aimed at providing high-quality vocational training with a focus on Persons with Disabilities (PwDs). In addtion, the objective is to enhance the skills of Persons with Disabilities by providing quality vocational skill training, enabling them to gain meaningful employment; empower PwDs to become self-reliant, productive, and contributing members of society.'),
	(913, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 6927, 'Assistance to Local Level Committee', 'Local Level Committees (LLCs) under the National Trust Act are empowered to provide assistance to individuals with disabilities, primarily in the areas of guardianship and welfare. '),
	(914, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 6969, 'Utthan Subsidy Scheme', 'The Utthan Subsidy Scheme generally refers to PM-KUSUM (Pradhan Mantri Kisan Urja Suraksha evam Utthaan Mahabhiyan), a government scheme aimed at promoting solar energy in agriculture. Specifically, it provides subsidies to farmers for installing solar irrigation pumps and other solar-based power generation systems. '),
	(915, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 6983, 'Treatment and Rehabilitation Institute for Cerebral Palsy Disabled Persons ', 'A treatment and rehabilitation institute for cerebral palsy (CP) disabled persons would offer a range of services to improve the quality of life for individuals with CP. These services typically include physiotherapy, occupational therapy, speech and language therapy, and other specialized therapies tailored to address the specific needs of each individual. '),
	(916, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 7014, 'Senior Citizen Assistance Scheme', 'The Senior Citizen Assistance Scheme, also known as the Indira Gandhi National Old Age Pension Scheme (IGNOAPS), is a social welfare program that provides financial assistance to eligible senior citizens. It\'s part of the National Social Assistance Programme (NSAP) and aims to support those living below the poverty line. '),
	(917, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 71, 'Schools for the Blind, Deaf and Dumb', 'Education to be provided to the blind deaf, dumb'),
	(918, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 73, 'Grants to NGO for the Blind, Deaf and Dumb', 'Grant provided to the blind, deaf and dumb for the welfare'),
	(919, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 7336, 'Indira Gandhi National Widow Pension', 'The scheme seeks to provide social security to widows of poor family (BPL)  of the society. A pension of Rs.3/- per month is provided to Widows between 4 years and 79 years. For persons who are 8 years and above the pension is Rs.5/- per month.'),
	(920, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 7340, 'Indira Gandhi National Disability Pension', 'The scheme seeks to provide monthly pension to disabled people for the prosperity of their lives.\n'),
	(921, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 7462, 'Establishment of State Resource and Rehabilitation Centre ', 'The establishment of State Resource and Rehabilitation Centres (SRRCs) is a scheme focused on providing comprehensive rehabilitation services to persons with disabilities at the state level. These centers aim to facilitate awareness, training, and the creation of infrastructure for disability rehabilitation'),
	(922, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 75, 'Scholarships for the blind and deaf', 'Stipends for the blind, deaf, and dumb (or people with disabilities in general) are often provided through government-funded scholarship schemes. '),
	(923, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 7589, 'Grant for Payment of Social Security Pension through Biometric Method in Urban Body Areas ', 'Payment of Social Security Pension '),
	(924, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 7613, 'Programs and Schemes related to Third Gender Community', 'The scheme seeks to provide facility to third gender community.'),
	(925, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 7735, 'Disabled Education Promotion Scheme', 'The scheme seeks to boos the quality of education for disabled popualtion'),
	(926, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 7737, 'Disabled People Civil Service Incentive Scheme', 'The "Incentive Scheme in Civil Service" by the Chhattisgarh Social Welfare Department aims to encourage persons with disabilities to pursue careers in civil services by providing financial support.'),
	(927, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 7738, 'Survey and Online Registration of Disabled People', 'The Indian government provides a platform for the online registration of persons with disabilities through the Unique Disability ID (UDID) project. This initiative aims to create a national database, streamline the process of obtaining disability certificates and UDID cards, and improve access to government benefits and services. '),
	(928, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 7739, 'Hostel Scheme for Disabled Students ', 'The "Student Housing Scheme for Students with Disabilities" provides free accommodation in rented buildings for eligible disabled students in Chhattisgarh. The scheme aims to encourage higher education among students with disabilities by offering hostel facilities. '),
	(929, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 7740, 'Disabled People Marriage Promotion Scheme', 'The Disabled Marriage Promotion Scheme, also known as the Disabled Wedding Incentive Scheme, provides financial assistance to persons with disabilities who marry. '),
	(930, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 7864, 'Chhattisgarh Yoga Commission', 'The scheme seeks to boost health and well-being'),
	(931, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 7886, 'Formation of Disabled Welfare Fund', 'The formation of a Disabled Welfare Fund involves establishing a dedicated financial resource to support programs and initiatives that benefit persons with disabilities. '),
	(932, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 79, 'Schools and institutions for visual and hearing aids', 'Several institutions cater to the needs of visually and hearing impaired individuals, including dedicated schools, integrated programs, and resource centers. These institutions focus on providing specialized education, vocational training, and support services to help individuals with sensory impairments achieve their full potential. '),
	(933, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 7917, 'Establishment of Hospice ', 'A home providing care for the sick or terminally ill.'),
	(934, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 7921, 'Chief Minister Pension Scheme', 'The scheme targets senior citizens, widows, and abandoned women listed on the basis of the survey list of Social, Economic and Caste Census 211. This scheme will be an additional scheme of the current Central and State Pension Scheme'),
	(935, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 8159, 'Additional Staff in the Headquarters for Effective Operation of Disabled Welfare Schemes', 'It aims to strengthen the institutional capacity for implementing disability welfare programs, ensuring better service delivery, inclusion, and support for persons with disabilities. Enhancing operational efficiency in disabled welfare schemes promotes social equity, reduces exclusion, and fosters inclusive governance'),
	(936, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 8662, 'Chhattisgarh Chief Minister Teerth Yojana', 'The scheme, launched by Chief Minister Vishnu Deo Sai, provides free pilgrimage travel, promoting social inclusion and equitable access to cultural and religious activities for marginalized and economically disadvantaged groups. This initiative supports mental and spiritual well-being, reduces inequalities by empowering vulnerable communities, and reflects inclusive governance'),
	(937, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 8664, 'Establishment of Physical Referral Rehabilitation Center in Mana', 'The main objectives of a rehabilitation center are to help individuals overcome challenges and improve their overall well-being, encompassing physical, mental, and social aspects. T'),
	(938, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 8665, 'Integrated Women Help Center for Mentally Ill Women (Parijat)', 'The Integrated Women Help Center for Mentally Ill Women, also known as Parijat, is a shelter home for women in distress, including those with mental illnesses, located in Raipur, Chhattisgarh. '),
	(939, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 8980, 'Gharaunda Scheme', 'The Gharaunda Scheme, also known as the Gharaunda-Group Home for Adults, is a program by the Department of Empowerment of Persons with Disabilities (Divyangjan) aimed at providing lifelong care and support for individuals with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental Retardation, and Multiple Disabilities. '),
	(940, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 8981, 'Protection of the Elderly', 'In India, the protection of the elderly is addressed through various laws and policies, primarily the Maintenance and Welfare of Parents and Senior Citizens Act, 27. '),
	(941, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 8990, 'Disability Self-Respect and Strength Scheme', 'The term "Disability Self-Respect and Strength Scheme" likely refers to various government initiatives aimed at promoting the well-being and empowerment of individuals with disabilities. '),
	(942, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 9142, 'Social Security and Welfare ', 'Social security and welfare are systems designed to protect individuals and families from financial hardship and ensure a basic standard of living. Social security typically involves mandatory, contributory programs like pensions and healthcare, while welfare refers to broader social safety nets, often funded by taxes, that provide assistance to those in need. '),
	(943, 'Social Welfare Department', NULL, 9605, 'Organ Grants to Non-Governmental Organisations (Scholarship Artificial Organs)', 'The scheme supports the provision of artificial organs and related scholarships, improving access to advanced healthcare and medical technology for patients in need. Such initiatives contribute to universal health coverage, enhance medical care quality.'),
	(944, 'Revenue Department', NULL, 4625, 'Operation of Permanent Daitv Grih Mana District Raipur', 'The scheme focuses on housing development and providing affordable residential buildings in Raipur, contributing to sustainable urban development and ensuring access to adequate, safe, and affordable housing for economically weaker sections.'),
	(945, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 1471, 'District Office', 'It strengthens local governance and administrative capacity for effective implementation of development programs.'),
	(946, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 3229, 'Reimbursement of Losses to Civil Supplies Corporation in Food Grain Procurement', 'The scheme supports food security by ensuring that food grain procurement operations remain financially viable, which helps maintain stable supply chains for essential food commodities. It also promotes sustainable agricultural practices and efficient resource use within the food system, contributing to ending hunger and promoting sustainable food production.'),
	(947, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 3248, 'Reimbursement of Losses to State Cooperative Marketing Federation in Food Grain Procurement', 'The scheme supports food security by ensuring that food grain procurement operations remain financially viable, which helps maintain stable supply chains for essential food commodities. It also promotes sustainable agricultural practices and efficient resource use within the food system, contributing to ending hunger and promoting sustainable food production.'),
	(948, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 3537, 'Head Office', 'The scheme supports administrative and governance functions at the central management level, strengthening institutional capacity, transparency, and accountability essential for effective implementation and coordination of development programs.'),
	(949, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 5456, 'Antyodaya Anna Yojana (AAY)', 'It is a public distribution system scheme that was implemented in India in 2. The main purpose of the system is to provide food security to the people and to end hunger in India.'),
	(950, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 6112, 'Head Office and Divisional Office', 'The scheme focus on enhancing governance, institutional capacity, and administrative efficiency.'),
	(951, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 629, 'Consumer Protection Cell', 'It is one of the many initiatives of Citizen Rights Protection Council. It is meant to help improve the quality of services being provided by various government and private enterprises'),
	(952, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 6401, 'Rice Fortification', 'The scheme aims to enhance the nutritional status of vulnerable populations, particularly those consuming rice as a staple. '),
	(953, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 6797, 'Financial Assistance for Consumer Awareness', '1. Creation of Consumer Law Chairs/ Centres of Excellence in Institutions/Universities of repute to foster research and training on consumer related issues. 2. Projects for spreading consumer literacy and awareness. 3. Grants for establishment of State Consumer Welfare (Corpus) Fund.'),
	(954, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 6839, 'Chief Minister Food Assistance Scheme', 'To ensure food security for the economically weaker and vulnerable families in the state of Chhattisgarh by providing rice and other food grains at subsidized or free rates,'),
	(955, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 6914, 'Assistance for Food Grain Storage in Inaccessible Areas during Rainy Season', 'The scheme seeks to provide assistance for constructing or renovating rural godowns to improve food grain storage in rural areas, particularly during the rainy season. In addition, the scheme also aims to reduce storage and transit losses and modernize food grain handling, storage, and transportation'),
	(956, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 6964, 'Assistance for Strengthening Public Distribution System', 'The scheme aims to enhance the facility for food security'),
	(957, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 7436, 'Provision of Gram under Antyodaya Anna Yojana', 'To provide nutritional support to the poorest families (AAY households) by distributing gram (chana) at subsidized rates, in addition to rice and wheat, under the Public Distribution System (PDS).'),
	(958, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 7800, 'Pradhan Mantri Ujjwala Yojana', 'objective to make clean cooking fuel such as LPG available to the rural and deprived households which were otherwise using traditional cooking fuels such as firewood, coal, cow-dung cakes etc. Usage of traditional cooking fuels had detrimental impacts on the health of rural women as well as on the environment.'),
	(959, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 7801, 'Price Stabilization Fund Scheme', 'The objective is to help regulate the price volatility of important agri-horticultural commodities. '),
	(960, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 7810, 'Chhattisgarh State Food Commission', 'It ensures the availability of food grains, sugar, salt, and other essential commodities at fair prices through Fair Price Shops. The commission also focuses on paddy and maize procurement from farmers at support prices and manages legal and budgetary matters related to food and consumer protection. '),
	(961, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 7872, 'P.D.S. Dealer Margin', 'The scheme refers to the commission or profit earned by a Fair Price Shop (FPS) dealer for distributing food grains to eligible beneficiaries.'),
	(962, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 7882, 'Price Monitoring Cell', 'The scheme focuses on monitoring retail and wholesale prices of essential food commodities to ensure price stability and availability, helping consumers and policymakers manage food affordability'),
	(963, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 7894, 'Financial Support to Fair Price Shops', 'The scheme aims to improve the viability and efficiency of Fair Price Shops (FPS) (also known as ration shops) by providing them with financial assistance and other support. '),
	(964, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 7906, 'Operation of Dal-Bhat Centers for Festivals/Fairs', 'The scheme supports food security and nutrition during large community events while promoting social inclusion and cultural sustainability.'),
	(965, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 7994, 'Jaggery Distribution Scheme', 'The objective of the \'Madhur Gud Yojana\' (Sweet Jaggery Scheme) in Chhattisgarh is to eradicate malnutrition and anemia, particularly among poor families in the Bastar division. '),
	(966, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 8545, 'Warehouse Construction with NABARD Assistance', 'The scheme provides financial assistance for warehouse construction through the Warehouse Infrastructure Fund (WIF). This fund supports the creation of storage infrastructure for agricultural commodities, including warehouses, silos, and cold storage facilities. '),
	(967, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 8674, 'Reimbursement of Expenses Incurred by State Cooperative Marketing Federation in Food Grain Procurement', 'The scheme seeks to boost food grain procurement, which will help in zero hunger.'),
	(968, 'Food, Civil Supplies Department ', NULL, 8919, 'Complete Computerization of Public Distribution System', 'The scheme seeks to boost digitalization in Public Distribution System.'),
