	(999, 'Culture Department', NULL, 7981, 'Sangrahalaya Bhavan Nirman (Museum Building Construction)', 'The objective is to boost the tourism industry'),
	(1000, 'Culture Department', NULL, 799, 'Artist Welfare Fund', 'The scheme seeks to reduce poverty by providing financial assistance to artists and litterateurs and their dependents'),
	(1001, 'Culture Department', NULL, 8975, 'Chh.G. Lok Kala Sangeet Academy evam Lokgeeto v Lok Nrityo ka Sanrakshan (Chh.G. Folk Art Music Academy and Conservation of Folk Songs and Folk Dances)', 'The scheme seeks to boost art and music industry, which will boost the economy by creating various opportunities.'),
	(1002, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 1831, 'Payment of Decree Money', 'The scheme supports the enforcement of judicial decisions by facilitating the timely payment of decree money awarded by courts. It helps ensure access to justice, uphold the rule of law, and strengthen effective, accountable, and transparent institutions at all levels.'),
	(1003, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 207, 'Other Minor Irrigation Construction Works', 'Minor irrigation construction works encompass a variety of projects focused on providing water for agriculture, especially in areas with limited access to larger water sources. These projects include building small dams, tanks, canals, and wells, as well as implementing water conservation and harvesting techniques. Drip irrigation, a method of delivering water directly to plant roots, is also considered a minor irrigation techniques'),
	(1004, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 2250, 'Canals and Ponds', 'Canals and ponds are both water features, but they differ in their characteristics and purposes. Canals are typically man-made channels designed for water transport, while ponds are natural or artificial bodies of standing water. '),
	(1005, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 2428, 'Execution Establishment (Unit One and Unit Two)', 'The scheme focuses on building resilient infrastructure, promoting inclusive and sustainable industrialization, and fostering innovation.'),
	(1006, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 275, 'Aviana Establishment', 'The scheme focuses on providing sustainable livelihood support, primarily aimed at ensuring food security for deprived and low-income households. It helps in the distribution of subsidized food grains through the public distribution system (PDS), targeting the poorest and vulnerable populations to reduce hunger and malnutrition'),
	(1007, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 2884, 'Canal and Related Construction Work', 'Canal construction involves the design and building of waterways for various purposes, including irrigation, drainage, and navigation. These projects often require specialized excavation, land surveying, and the use of heavy machinery. Key aspects include determining the canal\'s cross-section, ensuring proper slopes for water flow, and selecting appropriate lining materials like concrete'),
	(1008, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 2894, 'Dam and Canals', 'Types Of Dams » Civil Practical KnowledgeDams and canals are both vital components of water management systems, but they serve different purposes. Dams are barriers built across rivers to impound water, creating reservoirs for various uses like irrigation, flood control, and hydroelectric power generation. Canals, on the other hand, are engineered waterways designed to transport water from one location to another, often for irrigation or navigation'),
	(1009, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 2898, 'Dam and Releted Work', 'Dams are constructed for various purposes like water storage, flood control, irrigation, and power generation. They act as barriers to restrict water flow, creating reservoirs that can be used for multiple purposes. Related work includes dam design, construction, maintenance, rehabilitation, and managing the environmental and social impacts associated with these projects'),
	(1010, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 3264, 'Divisional Establishment', 'The scheme focuses on strengthening administrative and governance structures at the divisional level to ensure effective implementation of policies and development programs. By enhancing institutional capacity, transparency, and accountability, it supports inclusive and effective governance.'),
	(1011, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 3302, 'Divisional Establishment (Electrical Engineering)', 'The scheme aligns with goal 7, 8 and 9. The scheme supports the development and maintenance of electrical infrastructure, promotes energy access and efficiency, and fosters innovation in electrical engineering. By enhancing energy systems and industrial infrastructure, it contributes to clean and reliable energy supply, economic growth, job creation, and sustainable industrial development.'),
	(1012, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 3363, 'Survey of Medium Project', 'A survey of a medium project typically involves planning, designing, and conducting a survey to gather information and insights related to a project\'s scope, objectives, and progress. It can be used to assess risk, gather feedback, or analyze performance.'),
	(1013, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 3366, 'Construction Work of Medium Projects', 'Medium construction projects involve a scope between small and large projects, requiring more resources, time, and team coordination than smaller ones. These projects, often involving institutional or commercial buildings like hospitals, schools, or retail spaces, or specialized industrial facilities, demand careful planning, scheduling, and cost control. Effective project management, including risk mitigation and quality control, is crucial for success. '),
	(1014, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 3402, 'Machines and Equipments', 'The scheme supports the provision and maintenance of machinery and equipment to promote industrial development, technological progress, and infrastructure enhancement. By enabling access to modern tools and technologies, it fosters innovation.'),
	(1015, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 3556, 'Headquarter Establishment Unit One', 'The scheme supports strengthening institutional capacity and governance at the headquarters level, ensuring efficient administration and effective policy implementation. It promotes transparent, accountable, and inclusive institutions, which are essential for sustainable development and good governance.'),
	(1016, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 3803, 'Minor and Minimum Irrigation Schemes', 'Minor and minimum irrigation schemes refer to small-scale water management systems used for agricultural irrigation. They typically involve structures like wells, tube wells, tanks, and check dams, and are characterized by their limited command area, often up to 2, hectares. '),
	(1017, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 3828, 'Minor Irrigation Scheme', 'A minor irrigation scheme in India is an irrigation project with a culturable command area (CCA) of 2, hectares or less. These schemes play a vital role in India\'s overall irrigation potential and are crucial for agricultural development, particularly in providing timely and controlled water supply to crops. '),
	(1018, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 4416, 'Survey', 'The scheme aligns with goal 16 and 17. Surveys provide essential data and statistics that support evidence-based policy-making, monitoring, and evaluation of development programs. Reliable survey data contribute to transparent governance, informed decision-making, and effective implementation of the SDGs by enabling collaboration among government, civil society, and other stakeholders.'),
	(1019, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 4793, 'Water Meteorology Net Work and Directorate Establishment', 'The scheme seeks to support various aspects of water resource management, flood forecasting, disaster mitigation, and climate services. '),
	(1020, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 4843, 'Infrastructure Development Corporation', 'An Infrastructure Development Corporation is a company, often government-owned, focused on developing and improving various aspects of infrastructure, such as transportation networks, utilities, and other essential facilities. '),
	(1021, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 4948, 'Payment of Decree Money (Charged)', 'The scheme facilitates the enforcement of court decrees related to water resource management, ensuring justice and the rule of law in recovery of dues or compensation. By supporting effective legal and financial mechanisms, it promotes accountable institutions and fair governance.'),
	(1022, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 5059, 'Construction of Anicut / Stopdam', 'An Anicut, also known as a stop dam, is a low-height dam constructed across a river or stream to impound water for various purposes, primarily irrigation and flood control. '),
	(1023, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 5188, 'Medium Irrigation Project Construction Work (NABARD)', 'Medium irrigation projects, typically those with a cultivable command area (CCA) between 2, and 1, hectares, are often supported by NABARD through various schemes and funds like the Long-Term Irrigation Fund (LTIF). NABARD provides financial assistance, both as central and state share, for the completion of these projects, often in collaboration with state governments and other relevant bodies. '),
	(1024, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 5189, 'Minor Irrigation Scheme Construction Work (NABARD)', 'Minor irrigation schemes, often involving water harvesting, groundwater recharge, and surface water diversion, are crucial for agricultural development and are supported by NABARD through various financial and developmental initiatives. NABARD provides refinance to banks for minor irrigation projects and manages funds like the Micro Irrigation Fund (MIF) to expand irrigation coverage. '),
	(1025, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 541, 'Outstanding', 'The scheme focuses on ensuring sustainable water management, improving water availability, quality, and sanitation services. It supports targets such as universal access to safe and affordable drinking water, improved sanitation and hygiene, water-use efficiency, integrated water resource management, and protection of water-related ecosystems.'),
	(1026, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 5516, 'Major Irrigation Project Construction Work (NABARD)', 'NABARD (National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development) plays a significant role in funding and promoting major irrigation projects in India, particularly through the Long-Term Irrigation Fund (LTIF). This fund aims to expedite the completion of identified major and medium irrigation projects. NABARD also provides support for other irrigation initiatives, including micro-irrigation and diversion-based irrigation projects. '),
	(1027, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 5685, 'Dam Safety and Strengthening', 'Dam safety and strengthening focuses on ensuring the structural integrity and operational reliability of dams to prevent failure and protect downstream populations and infrastructure. This involves various aspects, including regular inspections, maintenance, and upgrades to address potential risks and enhance resilience. '),
	(1028, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 6354, 'Dam Rehabilitation and Improvement Project Phase-II', 'The Dam Rehabilitation and Improvement Project (DRIP) Phase II, is a project aimed at enhancing the safety and operational performance of existing dams in India, alongside strengthening dam safety initiatives. It is part of a larger initiative that includes Phase III, and is funded by a $25 million World Bank loan. The project focuses on physical rehabilitation of selected dams, institutional strengthening, and improving dam safety practices. '),
	(1029, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 6369, 'Construction and Restoration Work of Major Irrigation Schemes', 'Construction and restoration of major irrigation schemes involves various activities like building new canals, renovating existing ones, and modernizing outdated infrastructure to improve water distribution and irrigation potential. These projects often receive financial assistance from the central government under programs like the Accelerated Irrigation Benefits Programme (AIBP). '),
	(1030, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 6371, 'Construction and Restoration of Medium Irrigation Schemes', 'Construction and restoration of medium irrigation schemes in India are supported by the Pradhan Mantri Krishi Sinchayee Yojana (PMKSY), specifically through its Accelerated Irrigation Benefit Programme (AIBP). AIBP provides financial assistance for completing ongoing major and medium irrigation projects, as well as for Extension, Renovation, and Modernization (ERM) of existing projects. Additionally, the Repair, Renovation & Restoration (RRR) of Water Bodies sub-component of PMKSY focuses on restoring traditional water bodies'),
	(1031, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 6372, 'Construction and Restoration of Minor Irrigation Schemes', 'Construction and restoration of minor irrigation schemes focuses on developing or improving small-scale water management systems to enhance agricultural productivity and water resource availability, particularly in rural areas. These schemes include building new structures like tanks, canals, and wells, as well as renovating existing ones to increase their capacity and efficiency. '),
	(1032, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 6472, 'Groundwater Conservation Work', 'Groundwater conservation work involves various strategies and initiatives to ensure the sustainable use and replenishment of groundwater resources. These efforts are crucial due to increasing water scarcity, climate change impacts, and the need to protect this vital resource for future generations.'),
	(1033, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 6597, 'Lift Irrigation Project (Mega Lift)', 'The main objective of a Mega Lift Irrigation Project is to provide irrigation to large areas, particularly in upland regions, by lifting water from a source (like a river or canal) to a higher elevation where it can be distributed. These projects are often implemented in areas where traditional flow irrigation is not feasible due to topographical limitations'),
	(1034, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 6757, 'Flood Control Schemes', 'Flood control schemes involve a combination of structural and non-structural measures to mitigate flood damage. Structural measures include building dams, levees, and drainage systems, while non-structural measures involve flood forecasting, land use planning, and community preparedness. '),
	(1035, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 697, 'Tools and Plant', 'The scheme aligns goal 6 and 9. The scheme supports the provision, maintenance, and technological upgrading of tools and equipment essential for efficient water resource management, irrigation projects, and related infrastructure. By promoting the use of modern and efficient machinery, it contributes to sustainable water use, enhanced irrigation practices, infrastructure development, and agricultural productivity.'),
	(1036, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 7422, 'Industrial Water Structure Construction', 'Industrial water structure construction involves building infrastructure for water treatment, storage, and distribution for industrial purposes. This includes constructing water treatment plants, pipelines, reservoirs, and other related facilities. These structures are crucial for providing a reliable and safe water supply for various industrial processes, as well as treating wastewater before discharge. '),
	(1037, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 7684, 'Pradhan Mantri Krishi Sinchai Yojana (PMKSY)', 'The scheme mainly focuses on enhancing water use efficiency at the farm level through Micro Irrigation (Drip and Sprinkler Irrigation System). Besides, it also supports micro-level water storage, and water conservation/management activities (Other Interventions) to supplement source creation for Micro Irrigation.'),
	(1038, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 7820, 'Road and Bridge Construction', 'The "Road and Bridge Construction fund" typically refers to the Central Road and Infrastructure Fund (CRIF), which is the primary mechanism for funding road and bridge development and maintenance in India. This fund is managed by the Ministry of Road Transport and Highways and is financed through various sources including levies on petrol and diesel, toll collections, and monetization of national highways'),
	(1039, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 7953, 'Climate Sensitive Scheme', 'A Climate Sensitive Scheme refers to initiatives that acknowledge and address the impacts of climate change on specific sectors or populations, often integrating climate considerations into planning and implementation. These schemes can be national or local, and may focus on various aspects like agriculture, health, or infrastructure. '),
	(1040, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 814, 'Executive Establishment (Electrical Engineering)', 'The scheme alligns with goal 7, 8 and 9. The scheme supports the recruitment and establishment of skilled electrical engineering personnel who manage and develop the electrical infrastructure essential for efficient water resource management and irrigation projects. It promotes modern energy solutions, infrastructure development, and technical capacity, contributing to sustainable industrialization and economic growth.'),
	(1041, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 815, 'Executive Establishment', 'The scheme supports the establishment and strengthening of institutional and human resource capacity to manage water resources effectively. It contributes to sustainable water management, ensuring availability, quality, sanitation, and equitable access to water.'),
	(1042, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 8967, 'Anicut / Barrage', 'An Anicut, also known as a stop dam, is a low-height dam constructed across a river or stream to impound water for various purposes, primarily irrigation and flood control. They are smaller in scale compared to large dams and are often built to regulate water flow and create small reservoirs for local needs'),
	(1043, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 9469, 'Under Loan Assistance from NABARD', 'NABARD (National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development) provides loan assistance through various schemes to promote rural development and agriculture. These include long-term loans for infrastructure development, refinance for banks, and assistance for specific activities like agri-clinics and rural housing'),
	(1044, 'Housing and Environment Department ', 12, 2020, 'Town and Country Investment', 'The investment will boost economic growth.'),
	(1045, 'Housing and Environment Department ', 12, 5371, 'Naya Raipur Atal Nagar Development Authority', 'The scheme focuses on developing Naya Raipur (Atal Nagar) as a smart, green, and sustainable city with world-class infrastructure, efficient public services, inclusive governance, and environmental conservation. Key features include sustainable urban planning, eco-friendly practices.'),
	(1046, 'Housing and Environment Department ', 12, 6605, 'Real Estate Regulatory Appellate Tribunal, Raipur', 'The scheme seeks to boost infrastructutre.'),
	(1047, 'Housing and Environment Department ', 12, 6628, 'Naya Raipur Atal Nagar Smart City Corporation Limited', 'The scheme aligns primarily with goal 11. The scheme focuses on the development of Nava Raipur into a world-class, eco-friendly smart city with state-of-the-art infrastructure, including smart governance, efficient utility management, intelligent transport systems, city surveillance, and integrated command and control center (ICCC). The project emphasizes sustainable urban planning, environmental conservation, social inclusiveness.'),
	(1048, 'Housing and Environment Department ', 12, 7411, 'Grant to Development Authorities', 'The scheme aligns primarily with goal 11. The scheme provides financial support to development authorities to plan, develop, and manage urban infrastructure and services, promoting sustainable urbanization, improved housing, transportation, and public utilities. By enabling well-planned and inclusive urban development, it supports targets related to making cities safe, resilient, and sustainable.'),
	(1049, 'Housing and Environment Department ', 12, 7416, 'Grant received under the recommendation of Thirteenth Finance Commission', 'The scheme aligns primarily with goal 11 and 16. The scheme aims to strengthen urban local bodies and improve municipal governance through financial grants that support urban services such as solid waste management, sanitation, urban forestry, school infrastructure, and overall planned urban growth. The performance-based grants encourage transparency, accountability, and efficiency in urban governance, thereby promoting sustainable, inclusive, and resilient urban development.'),
	(1050, 'Housing and Environment Department ', 12, 7444, 'Vikas Nagar Yojana (Development Town Scheme)', 'The scheme aims to foster development in Vikas Nagar.'),
	(1051, 'Housing and Environment Department ', 12, 7669, 'Sewerage Treatment Plant in Naya Raipur', 'The scheme aims to boost clean waster and sanitation in Nava Raipur.'),
	(1052, 'Housing and Environment Department ', 12, 7670, 'Chief Minister Housing Scheme', 'The scheme aligns primarily with goal 11. The scheme focuses on providing affordable, safe, and durable housing to low-income and vulnerable populations, improving their living conditions and promoting inclusive urban and rural development. It supports targets related to ensuring access to adequate, safe, and affordable housing and basic services, reducing slum dwellings, and enhancing sustainable urbanization'),
	(1053, 'Housing and Environment Department ', 12, 8635, 'Maintenance of New Ministry', 'The scheme focuses on maintaining and strengthening institutional capacities and administrative infrastructure within ministries, which supports effective governance, accountability, and transparency. Such institutional strengthening is essential for building inclusive and strong institutions that can efficiently implement sustainable development policies and programs.'),
	(1054, 'Housing and Environment Department ', 12, 8892, 'Chhattisgarh Rent Control Tribunal', 'The scheme establishes a tribunal to adjudicate rent-related disputes, ensuring fair and timely resolution of conflicts between landlords and tenants. It promotes access to justice, upholds the rule of law, and strengthens institutional mechanisms for dispute settlement in the housing sector.'),
