	(1068, 'Public Health and Engineering Department', NULL, 3396, 'Reserved Water Supply/ Toilet arrangement for fairs', 'The scheme aims to promote fairs and exhibitions by ensuring adequate and accessible toilet and water supply facilities to safeguard public health and convenience. It includes designated toilets for men and women, as well as disabled access, equipped with proper handwashing stations and sufficient water supply. Furthermore, effective waste disposal and cleaning services are essential components to maintain a hygienic environment.'),
	(1069, 'Public Health and Engineering Department', NULL, 3862, 'Public Health Engineering Laboratories', 'The "Public Health Engineering Laboratories scheme" likely refers to initiatives aimed at establishing and improving laboratories for testing water quality and other public health-related parameters within the Public Health Engineering Department (PHED) framework. These labs are crucial for ensuring safe drinking water and sanitation, playing a vital role in rural water supply programs and overall public health. '),
	(1070, 'Public Health and Engineering Department', NULL, 4058, 'Advances in various public works', 'Public works advancements encompass a wide range of areas, from traditional infrastructure like roads and bridges to digital initiatives and urban development projects. These advancements aim to improve the quality of life for citizens, stimulate economic growth, and enhance the efficiency of public services. '),
	(1071, 'Public Health and Engineering Department', NULL, 4184, 'Survey of water supply and drainage scheme in urban and semi-urban areas', 'A survey of urban and semi-urban water supply and drainage schemes involves assessing the availability, accessibility, and quality of water sources, as well as the effectiveness of drainage infrastructure in handling stormwater and wastewater. This includes evaluating existing systems, identifying areas of improvement, and planning for future needs, often incorporating sustainable practices. '),
