	(1507, 'Public Health and Family Welfare Department', 10, 7154, 'Pradhan Mantri Tribal Justice Maha Campaingn Program', 'The objective is to improve the socio-economic conditions of Particularly Vulnerable Tribal Groups (PVTGs) by providing access to basic facilities and improving infrastructure in their villages. This includes ensuring access to safe housing, clean drinking water, improved healthcare, education, nutrition, road and telecom connectivity, and sustainable livelihood opportunities.'),
	(1508, 'Public Health and Family Welfare Department', 10, 7190, 'Establishment of Mobile Health Unit in Neyyad Nellnar', 'The primary objective of establishing a Mobile Health Unit (MHU) is to extend healthcare services to underserved populations, particularly those in remote, rural, or geographically challenging areas where access to traditional healthcare facilities is limited. This involves providing a range of preventive, promotive, and curative healthcare services directly to communities, thereby improving health outcomes and reducing health disparities. '),
	(1509, 'Public Health and Family Welfare Department', 10, 7213, 'Matritva Vandana Yojana', 'The scheme is to provide maternity benefits to women belonging to socially and economically disadvantaged sections of society. The maternity benefit is to be provided to a woman for the first two living children provided the second child is a girl.'),
