	(1528, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 6912, 'Construction of building of District/Block Education Officer', 'The construction of a District/Block Education Officer\'s building is not a standard, centrally mandated project. While the District Education Office (DEO) and Block Education Officer (BEO) are crucial for educational administration, their offices are typically established within existing government buildings or rented spaces. The focus of educational initiatives is on improving the quality of education through teacher training, infrastructure development in schools, and providing resources, rather than constructing separate buildings for these administrative roles'),
	(1529, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7119, 'PM Janman Yojana', 'The scheme is a government initiative focused on improving the socio-economic conditions of Particularly Vulnerable Tribal Groups (PVTGs). Its objective is to provide PVTGs, over a period of three years, with secure housing, clean drinking water, education, health, nutrition, better road and telecommunications connectivity, electrification of homes without electricity, and sustainable livelihood opportunities.'),
	(1530, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7121, 'Administrative Expenses', 'The scheme aligns primarily with goal 16. Effective administrative expenditure supports the efficient functioning of government institutions, promoting transparency, accountability, and strong governance systems necessary for sustainable development. The scheme also indirectly support goal 17 by ensuring well-managed public finance systems that facilitate cooperation and coordination among various stakeholders to achieve development objectives'),
	(1531, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7156, 'Backward Class Welfare Commission', 'The National Commission for Backward Classes (NCBC) is a constitutional body in India dedicated to the welfare and advancement of socially and educationally backward classes, also known as Other Backward Classes (OBCs). '),
	(1532, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 7169, 'Dharti Abba Tribal Village Development Campaign', 'The scheme aims to reduce inequality by providing support in infrastructure, health, education, and livelihood.'),
	(1533, 'Tribal Scheduled Caste and Backward Classes Department', NULL, 9840, 'Construction of Buildings for Educational Institutions', 'The objective of constructing buildings for educational institutions is to create safe, functional, and inspiring spaces that support effective learning and community engagement. '),
	(1534, 'Water Resources Department ', 23, 9284, 'Tube Well Construction', 'Types of Wells: Learn About Open Well, Tubewell And Their TypesThe primary objective of tube well construction is to create a reliable and sustainable source of groundwater for various uses, including irrigation, domestic water supply, and industrial applications. This involves creating a borehole and installing a casing with a screen to extract water from an underground aquifer. ');
