	(201, 'SIF_TARGET214', '15.1.2 Protected area as percentage of total geographical area', NULL, 0.000000000000000000000000000000, 'Forest Survey of India 2015, Ministry of Environment Forest and Climate Change, GoI', 'Percentage', 'yearly', 'N', 8.860000000000000000000000000000, 18, 8, 'The indicator refers as protected area as percentage of total geographic area . Protected area â€“ 11984.3 Sq. KM\nGeographical area â€“ 135192 Sq. KM\nNumerator: Total area under National Park and Wild Life Sanctuaries Denominator: Total Geographic Area\nMultiplier: 100\nProtected areas are those in which human occupation or at least the exploitation of resources is limited. There are several kinds of protected areas, which vary by level of protection depending on the enabling laws of each country or the regulations of the international organizations involved. The term â€œprotected areaâ€ also includes Marine Protected Areas, the boundaries of which will include some area of ocean, and Trans boundary Protected Areas that overlap multiple countries which remove\nthe borders inside the area for conservation and economic purposes.', 'Forest Survey of India 2019, Ministry of Environment Forest and Climate Change, GoI', 'https://www.fsi.nic.in/forest -report-2015 // https://www.fsi.nic.in/forest -report-2019', 'Total area under National Park and Wild Life Sanctuaries', 'Total Geographic Area\r\nMultiplier: 100\r\n'),
	(202, 'SIF_TARGET215', '15.2.1 Percentage change in Forest Cover (decadal) (%)', 0.00, 0.000000000000000000000000000000, 'Forest Survey of India 2015, Ministry of Environment Forest and Climate Change, GoI', 'Percentage', 'yearly', 'N', -0.020000000000000000000000000000, 18, 8, 'The \'Forest Area\' or \'Recorded Forest Area (RFA)\' refers to all the geographic areas recorded as \'Forests\' in government records. RFA mainly consists of Reserved Forests (RF)and Protected Forests (PF), which have been notified under the provisions of Indian Forest Act, 1927 or its counterpart State Acts. Besides RFs & PFs, the RFA may also include all such areas, which have been recorded as forests in the revenue records or have been constituted so under any State Act or Local Laws. The data for this indicator is collected by Forest Survey of India.\nNumerator: Recorded Forest Area in the period t -Recorded Forest Area in period (t-2) Denominator: Recorded Forest Area in the period t-Recorded Forest Area in period (t-2) Multiplier: 100\nNote: \'t\' refers to reference time period', 'Forest Survey of India 2019, Ministry of Environment Forest and Climate Change, GoI', 'https://www.fsi.nic.in/forest-report-2015', 'Recorded Forest Area in the period t -Recorded Forest Area in period (t-2)', 'Recorded Forest Area in the period t-Recorded Forest Area in period (t-2) Multiplier: 100\r\n'),
	(203, 'SIF_TARGET215', '15.2.3 Tree cover as percentage of total geographical area', 33.00, 0.000000000000000000000000000000, 'Forest Survey of India 2015, Ministry of Environment Forest and Climate Change, GoI', 'Ratio', 'yearly', 'N', 2.680000000000000000000000000000, 18, 8, 'The indicator refers as the tree cover as percentage of total geographical area\nNumerator: Total tree cover Denominator: Total Geographic Area Multiplier: 100', 'Forest Survey of India 2019, Ministry of Environment Forest and Climate Change,\nGoI', 'https://www.fsi.nic.in/forest -report-2015 // https://www.fsi.nic.in/forest -report-2019', 'Total tree cover', 'otal Geographic Area Multiplier: 100'),
	(204, 'SIF_TARGET210', '13.1.1 Number of districts where outreach programmes are conducted', NULL, 0.000000000000000000000000000000, 'Department of Revenue & Disaster Management, Government of Chhattisgarh', 'Number', 'yearly', 'N', 27.000000000000000000000000000000, 28, NULL, 'The indicator highlights the number of districts inIndia who\nhave prepared their State Action Plan on Climate Change (SAPCC) in order to enable the mselvesto address existing as well as future climate change and reduce the associated risks and vulnerabilities. The framework for SAPCC includes three main components:\na) Climate profile of the state b) Climate change strategy c) Climate change action plan', 'Department of Revenue & Disaster Management, Government of Chhattisgarh', '', NULL, NULL),
	(205, 'SIF_TARGET214', '15.1.1 Forest cover as a percentage of total geographical area, (in percentage)', 50.00, 0.000000000000000000000000000000, 'Forest Survey of India 2015, Ministry of Environment Forest and Climate Change, GoI', 'Percentage', 'yearly', 'N', 41.120000000000000000000000000000, 18, 8, 'Numerator: Recorded Forest Area Denominator: Total geographical area Multiplier: 100\nForest cover is defined as â€˜All Lands, more than 1 ha. in area, with a tree canopy density of more than 10% irrespective of ownership and legal status. Such land may not necessarily be a recorded forest area. It also includes orchards, bamboo and\npalmâ€™.', 'Forest Survey of India 2019, Ministry of Environment Forest and Climate Change,\nGoI', 'https://www.fsi.nic.in/forest -report-2015 // https://www.fsi.nic.in/forest -report-2019', 'Recorded Forest Area', 'Total geographical area Multiplier: 100\r\n'),
